# CAP Manifest and Packaging Rules

## manifest.json — Required Fields

Every manifest.json must contain all of these fields:

```json
{
  "name": "app-name",           // kebab-case, unique in registry
  "displayName": "App Name",    // human-readable
  "domain": "tax",              // tax, shipping, payment, fraud, etc.
  "description": "...",         // short description
  "version": "1.0.0",          // semantic version (MAJOR.MINOR.PATCH)
  "zip": "app-name-v1.0.0.zip", // must match [name]-v[version].zip
  "sha256": "..."               // SHA256 hash of the ZIP file
}
```

## Version Naming

- Semantic versioning: `MAJOR.MINOR.PATCH`
- ZIP filename: `[name]-v[version].zip` (e.g., `avalara-tax-v0.2.2.zip`)
- The `version` field must match the version in the ZIP filename
- The `name` field must match the name prefix in the ZIP filename
- Each version must have a unique ZIP filename — never reuse filenames

## SHA256 Integrity

- The `sha256` field must be the SHA256 hash of the actual ZIP file
- Generate with: `shasum -a 256 [filename].zip` (macOS) or `sha256sum [filename].zip` (Linux)
- Always regenerate after any change to the ZIP contents

## catalog.json

- New apps must include `catalog.json` with INIT values:
  ```json
  { "latest": { "version": "INIT", "tag": "INIT" }, "versions": [] }
  ```
- Do NOT modify catalog.json for version updates — CI automation handles this
- CI creates Git tags matching the ZIP filename without `.zip`

## ZIP Contents

- Top-level directory should include app name and version
- Must exclude: `.DS_Store`, `__MACOSX/`, `Thumbs.db`, `.git/`, `.env`, `node_modules/`
- Must include `README.md` with installation instructions
- Backend apps must include both `impex/install/` and `impex/uninstall/`
- Backend cartridges must have `package.json` pointing to `hooks.json`
- Frontend extensions must have `target-config.json` and Storybook stories
- All source files must include the Apache 2.0 copyright header

## Registry Directory Structure

- Apps are organized by domain: `tax/[app-name]/`, `shipping/[app-name]/`
- Each app directory contains: ZIP, manifest.json, catalog.json
- Domain directory names are lowercase

## Submission Validation

Before submitting a PR, verify:
- `sha256` matches: run `shasum -a 256` on the ZIP and compare
- `version` is consistent between manifest.json and ZIP filename
- `name` is consistent between manifest.json and ZIP filename
- No internal Salesforce release numbers in README or documentation
- No hardcoded credentials anywhere in the package
